19:22.458 --> 19:24.291
-Bye, Dad.
-MARK MOSSBACHER: Bye.

19:32.000 --> 19:33.333
Mr. Mossbacher.

19:35.458 --> 19:36.458
How are you?

19:39.375 --> 19:40.708
I'm a little hungover.

19:43.000 --> 19:44.375
But not too bad.

19:47.500 --> 19:48.791
Well, you look great.

19:51.875 --> 19:52.958
Thank you.

19:55.208 --> 19:56.208
So do you.

20:11.208 --> 20:12.541
Well, have a good one.

20:15.541 --> 20:16.791
I'll see you soon.

20:30.291 --> 20:32.250
BELINDA: (WHISPERING)
Pardon me, so sorry.

20:32.666 --> 20:33.750
Thank you.

20:33.833 --> 20:35.416
-Tanya, hi.
-Oh.

20:35.500 --> 20:37.583
I thought you might enjoy
some peppermint tea

20:37.666 --> 20:40.083
-before your wrap.
-TANYA: Oh, thank you.

20:40.166 --> 20:42.375
Of course. Good to see you.

20:47.166 --> 20:49.958
Yeah. Helps with... circulation.

20:51.500 --> 20:55.083
(EXHALES) Yeah.
I just love peppermint tea.

20:57.750 --> 20:59.416
It's good.

20:59.500 --> 21:02.666
I just really wanna thank you
for yesterday.

21:02.750 --> 21:06.166
And being there for me,
getting me to my room.

21:06.250 --> 21:08.708
-I mean, I was a mess.
-You were fine.

21:08.791 --> 21:11.625
TANYA: It would've been
a hell of a lot worse
if you hadn't been there.

21:11.708 --> 21:15.041
You have, like,
a really beautiful,

21:15.125 --> 21:17.666
kind, and calming presence.

21:17.750 --> 21:19.625
Seriously, Belinda.
I'm not kidding.

21:19.708 --> 21:22.000
You-- you should have
your own wellness center.

21:22.083 --> 21:23.041
You should.

21:23.125 --> 21:25.041
Because you really know
what you're doing.

21:25.125 --> 21:26.791
That's really very sweet.
Thank you.

21:26.875 --> 21:30.625
You just can't be behind
the desk at some hotel spa.

21:30.708 --> 21:32.666
You need to be in business
for yourself.

21:33.250 --> 21:34.375
I know.

21:34.458 --> 21:37.791
Yeah, and hey, I'm someone
who can make that happen.

21:38.750 --> 21:40.958
You should really
think about it.

21:42.625 --> 21:43.666
(CHUCKLES)

21:43.750 --> 21:45.625
It's something I could use.

21:46.791 --> 21:49.291
You know, I could have
a lot of fun too,

21:49.375 --> 21:52.500
and I could, you know,
even give you a couple ideas.

21:52.583 --> 21:55.166
You know,
the whole vision could be yours.

21:58.000 --> 21:59.333
I'm flattered.

21:59.416 --> 22:02.000
And I'm very much interested.

22:02.083 --> 22:06.708
Hey, one sec. Yeah, um--
I, uh-- I gotta have, um...

22:06.791 --> 22:08.500
You drink
the peppermint tea for now,

22:08.583 --> 22:10.500
and, um, I wanna
talk about this more,

22:10.583 --> 22:14.291
but I'll be way more clear
after my oxygen facial.

22:14.833 --> 22:16.625
Okay. All right.

22:18.833 --> 22:21.166
Let's get into business!
Okay.

22:25.750 --> 22:28.500
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

22:31.833 --> 22:32.708
What the fuck?

22:32.791 --> 22:34.291
The bong is here,
the weed is here,

22:34.375 --> 22:35.625
but the pills are gone.

22:35.708 --> 22:38.041
No. What about the K?

22:38.125 --> 22:39.708
Do you think that fucker
took our stash?

22:39.791 --> 22:41.750
The Klonopin, Liv.

22:41.833 --> 22:43.083
NICOLE MOSSBACHER:
How's it going?

22:51.000 --> 22:53.041
Hey, can I ask you girls
a favor?

22:54.750 --> 22:57.125
Can you try to include Quinn
a little bit more

22:57.208 --> 22:59.583
in your voodoo ceremonies
and whatever else you do?

22:59.666 --> 23:02.125
Mom, he's scuba diving
in the kiddie pool.

23:02.208 --> 23:05.666
No, I know, just in general.
You know, I just...

23:05.750 --> 23:08.291
I don't think you appreciate
how tough things are

23:08.375 --> 23:10.416
for kids like Quinn right now.

23:10.500 --> 23:12.458
Why? Because of the Asperger's?

23:12.541 --> 23:15.291
He doesn't have Asperger's,
Olivia.

23:15.375 --> 23:18.833
But he is a straight, white,
young man.

23:18.916 --> 23:21.416
And nobody has any sympathy
for them right now.

23:21.500 --> 23:23.625
And I just feel like we should.

23:24.833 --> 23:27.708
Yeah, in a way,
they're the underdogs now.

23:29.291 --> 23:30.291
Go on.

23:30.375 --> 23:32.625
Well, for instance,
young guys like Quinn,

23:32.708 --> 23:34.083
who are just
getting out of college,

23:34.166 --> 23:36.791
I don't care how incredibly
impressive they are,

23:36.875 --> 23:40.250
it is almost impossible
for us to hire them.

23:40.333 --> 23:42.458
Well, isn't that
because up until now,

23:42.541 --> 23:44.500
they're the only people
that you've ever hired?

23:44.583 --> 23:46.416
Yeah, don't you have
enough of them on staff?

23:46.500 --> 23:47.500
Trust me, I get it.

23:47.583 --> 23:52.833
I'm just saying,
I understand how guys like Quinn

23:52.916 --> 23:55.666
can feel a little alienated
from the culture right now.

23:56.125 --> 23:57.333
Mom, cringe.

23:57.416 --> 24:00.000
And I don't think
it's fair to him.

24:00.083 --> 24:01.375
Mom, cringe.

24:01.458 --> 24:04.750
(SIGHS)
Olivia, he's my son, okay?

24:06.041 --> 24:08.333
I think
he's gonna be okay, Nicole.

24:09.125 --> 24:10.166
Thank you, Paula.

24:11.208 --> 24:13.416
Okay. Paula's meds are missing.

24:13.500 --> 24:15.958
And so we need to go find them.
It's urgent.

24:16.041 --> 24:17.916
She's not gonna have
like a seizure or something?

24:18.000 --> 24:19.583
If I keep sitting here.

24:20.833 --> 24:23.291
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

24:25.041 --> 24:27.000
(WAVES CRASHING)

24:31.958 --> 24:33.625
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

24:36.291 --> 24:38.541
Now, I know you said
you didn't want my surprise,

24:38.625 --> 24:41.041
but I took the liberty
of bringing it anyway.

24:41.916 --> 24:42.958
What is it?

24:43.625 --> 24:44.833
Well...

24:45.625 --> 24:46.916
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

24:47.500 --> 24:49.291
-Ta-da!
-Mom.

24:49.375 --> 24:51.000
-Am I interrupting?
-SHANE: Mom.

24:51.083 --> 24:52.666
KITTY PATTON:
I know it's only your honeymoon.

24:52.750 --> 24:54.833
SHANE:
What are you doing here? Hey!

24:54.916 --> 24:56.416
KITTY: Aw.

24:56.500 --> 24:58.125
Listen,
I know this isn't kosher,

24:58.208 --> 24:59.833
and I told him
to keep it a secret

24:59.916 --> 25:02.333
because I knew you would say no.

25:02.416 --> 25:04.750
Get outta here. Come on,
come on, come on, come on.

25:04.833 --> 25:06.416
ARMOND:
Dinner reservation for three?

25:06.500 --> 25:07.583
SHANE: Yeah.

25:08.125 --> 25:09.166
Rach.

25:09.250 --> 25:11.875
Surprise! (GIGGLES)

25:11.958 --> 25:14.708
Oh, my God.
Look at her face, poor thing.

25:14.791 --> 25:16.375
She's white as a sheet.

25:17.333 --> 25:19.916
Don't worry. I have my own room.

25:20.000 --> 25:22.875
And I'm here just one night,
maybe two nights.

25:22.958 --> 25:24.958
I'm crazy. I'm so sorry.

25:25.041 --> 25:27.083
I'm totally crazy. I know.

25:27.166 --> 25:28.833
I was just so tense
from the wedding

25:28.916 --> 25:30.541
and all the weeks
leading up to it.

25:30.625 --> 25:31.666
I know you were too.

25:32.458 --> 25:33.666
And then Cathy Clement--

25:33.750 --> 25:35.625
I swear
this was Cathy Clement's idea.

25:35.708 --> 25:38.208
She said, "We should do
a spa week at the Mauna Kea."

25:38.291 --> 25:40.375
And of course
that sounded amazing.

25:40.458 --> 25:42.208
And then I talked to you
on the phone, honey,

25:42.291 --> 25:45.416
and you sounded so upset.
You had me worried.

25:45.500 --> 25:48.791
And I thought, you know,
maybe I'll just pop over

25:48.875 --> 25:51.916
and see you guys for a second
and give you a little love

25:52.000 --> 25:53.291
and then be on my way

25:53.375 --> 25:55.166
and go meet Cathy
at the Mauna Kea.

25:55.250 --> 25:57.083
Please don't be mad
at your mother-in-law.

25:57.166 --> 25:59.333
Oh, my God.
Of course not. I'm not mad.

25:59.416 --> 26:01.208
I'm really,
really happy to see you.

26:01.291 --> 26:03.416
Oh, good.
That makes me so happy.

26:03.500 --> 26:05.041
This is a really nice view.

26:05.916 --> 26:07.583
It's a really nice room.

26:07.666 --> 26:10.125
But it's definitely
not the room I booked.

26:11.125 --> 26:12.208
Trust me, I know.

26:12.291 --> 26:13.958
Why did they
give you this room, I wonder?

26:14.041 --> 26:16.958
Mother... (SCOFFS)
Don't even start.

26:17.500 --> 26:18.541
It's...

26:22.000 --> 26:24.125
Hmm? It's a touchy subject, huh?

26:24.208 --> 26:25.291
SHANE: Yeah.

26:27.250 --> 26:30.083
I can't believe
my baby boy is married.

26:30.166 --> 26:32.375
-I can't believe it! Aw.
-(SHANE CHUCKLES)

26:32.458 --> 26:34.375
I am so glad
we had so many cameras.

26:34.458 --> 26:37.333
The whole thing
is an absolute blur.

26:37.416 --> 26:40.625
I don't remember anything.
Do you? Do you?

26:40.708 --> 26:43.458
And Rachel,
you were such a beautiful bride,

26:43.541 --> 26:44.791
but also very pale.

26:44.875 --> 26:46.500
But now you have
a little more color,
and it looks great.

26:46.583 --> 26:49.000
-Thanks.
-Have you been in the ocean?
Have you been surfing, Shane?

26:49.083 --> 26:49.958
SHANE: Little bit.

26:50.041 --> 26:51.291
I really worry
about your ears, though.

26:51.375 --> 26:52.958
You really have to wear--
Did you get earplugs?

26:53.041 --> 26:53.958
SHANE: I know.

26:54.041 --> 26:55.666
I really like
this textured paper

26:55.750 --> 26:57.333
over here on this wall.

26:57.416 --> 27:00.041
So pretty.
I wanna get that, don't you?

27:01.208 --> 27:03.875
Gives it some character.

27:03.958 --> 27:05.958
(EXHALES)
And all the palm fronds.

27:06.041 --> 27:08.541
-It is the Palm Suite.
-It's a theme, there you go.

27:08.625 --> 27:10.625
-(GIGGLES)
-(SHANE CHUCKLES)

27:10.708 --> 27:12.041
KITTY: Ooh, what's out here?

27:12.125 --> 27:14.041
-What?
-KITTY: Oh, pretty.

27:14.125 --> 27:16.791
But so many plants
are obstructing the view.

27:23.625 --> 27:26.541
Buddy, Quinn, yesterday...

27:28.250 --> 27:30.791
I think I said some things
that I probably shouldn't have.

27:30.875 --> 27:33.166
-Like what?
-MARK: Well...

27:34.250 --> 27:38.333
I don't really remember
exactly what I said, so...

27:38.416 --> 27:40.625
You said having sex with mom
was like

27:40.708 --> 27:42.583
eating a plate of live worms.

27:44.125 --> 27:45.166
I said that?

27:51.250 --> 27:54.375
Quinn, look, okay, that's not
because of your mother.

27:54.458 --> 27:57.625
Your mother is beautiful.
Like, I'm lucky.

27:59.500 --> 28:01.041
I mean, the truth is...

28:05.333 --> 28:06.791
Do you wanna know the truth?

28:08.083 --> 28:09.083
Okay.

28:10.041 --> 28:12.541
I cheated on your--
your mother once.

28:14.500 --> 28:17.583
Well, not once,
but with one woman.

28:19.416 --> 28:21.416
You know, a few times.

28:21.500 --> 28:23.375
Um, a couple--
it was a couple of times.

28:23.458 --> 28:25.208
-You did?
-Yeah.

28:27.958 --> 28:28.916
Does Mom know?

28:29.000 --> 28:30.875
Yeah, she knows.
Of course she knows.

28:32.125 --> 28:35.125
And dealing with it,
dealing with her,

28:35.208 --> 28:37.250
getting her
to forgive me, was...

28:37.833 --> 28:39.333
it was hell.

28:40.625 --> 28:41.583
(SCOFFS)

28:41.666 --> 28:43.416
It was the worst time
in my life.

28:44.541 --> 28:46.458
We managed to keep you kids
in the dark,

28:46.541 --> 28:48.208
but she almost left me.

28:51.375 --> 28:53.750
And, you know,
there was a lot of drama.

28:53.833 --> 28:55.541
We had to do all this therapy.

28:55.625 --> 28:59.041
Yeah, I bought her a pair
of bracelets for 75,000 dollars.

28:59.125 --> 29:00.125
What?

29:01.333 --> 29:02.958
Yeah. With my money.

29:03.041 --> 29:04.375
Not her money.

29:04.458 --> 29:06.208
♪ ("NANI WALE LIHUE"
BY THE ROSE ENSEMBLE PLAYING) ♪

29:06.291 --> 29:08.333
Man... (SIGHS)
...in the moment...

29:09.666 --> 29:10.916
you're like this...

29:12.375 --> 29:13.458
You're a monkey.

29:14.708 --> 29:16.500
<i>Like possessed.</i>

29:16.583 --> 29:19.166
You'd do anything
to get your rocks off.

29:20.500 --> 29:22.708
<i>And then, later, you regret it.</i>

29:24.083 --> 29:25.500
And you do regret it.

29:25.583 --> 29:29.166
♪ (VOCALIST SINGING
IN HAWAIIAN) ♪

29:29.250 --> 29:31.750
There's the man,
and there's the monkey.

29:33.750 --> 29:36.250
And somehow,
you gotta be man enough

29:36.333 --> 29:37.833
to face down the monkey.

29:44.666 --> 29:46.125
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

29:49.833 --> 29:51.541
GREG: Fuck you! Shit!

29:52.458 --> 29:54.041
Really? Come on.

29:54.125 --> 29:56.416
What the hell? Come on.

29:56.500 --> 29:58.583
-Hello?
-(DOOR RATTLING)

30:00.666 --> 30:02.625
-Come on!
-Excuse me.

30:03.791 --> 30:05.583
I think this is my room.

30:08.208 --> 30:13.083
Oh, crap. Well, where am I?
What am I doing?

30:13.166 --> 30:16.083
Well, no wonder
it's not working. (LAUGHS)

30:16.625 --> 30:18.041
I'm so confused.

30:19.250 --> 30:23.041
Five nine four!
I'm five nine two.

30:23.125 --> 30:25.458
I was drinking on the boat.
(LAUGHS)

30:25.541 --> 30:26.666
Oh yeah?

30:26.750 --> 30:28.750
Yeah, I'm sorry about that.
I'll get out of your way.

30:28.833 --> 30:31.958
I think I must be one over.

30:32.041 --> 30:33.250
Maybe this way here.

30:33.333 --> 30:36.375
Oh, yeah, this is me. Sorry.
(LAUGHS)

30:36.458 --> 30:39.166
-We were drinking on the boat.
-Oh, yeah?

30:39.250 --> 30:40.750
You said that. (CHUCKLES)

30:40.833 --> 30:43.250
Yeah, we go on a deep-sea
fishing trip every year.

30:43.333 --> 30:44.666
Just a good group of guys.

30:44.750 --> 30:46.500
Bunch of buds from the BLM.

30:47.708 --> 30:50.916
Oh. (LAUGHS) Oh.

30:51.000 --> 30:54.583
(CHUCKLES) You enjoying Hawaii?
You-- you here with your family?

30:56.500 --> 30:59.750
No. No, I'm vacationing
with myself.

30:59.833 --> 31:01.416
GREG: Oh, okay. Yeah.

31:01.500 --> 31:03.666
-My family's not here either.
-TANYA: Oh.

31:03.750 --> 31:06.916
My kids are grown, wife's gone.
I'm divorced.

31:07.541 --> 31:08.750
Oh.

31:08.833 --> 31:12.083
Sorry about getting
in your... door.

31:12.166 --> 31:14.041
-(ELECTRONIC BEEP)
-There we go. It worked!

31:15.833 --> 31:17.041
(DOOR OPENS)

31:24.041 --> 31:25.958
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

31:35.416 --> 31:38.333
GREG: Hi. Hi. So, listen.

31:38.416 --> 31:40.250
You know, my friends,
they're leaving today,

31:40.333 --> 31:42.416
and I'm gonna be staying here
until the weekend,

31:42.500 --> 31:43.875
and you're alone,
and I figured,

31:43.958 --> 31:45.541
well, why don't we just go
grab dinner?

31:45.625 --> 31:47.083
You wanna grab dinner tonight?

31:47.833 --> 31:48.916
Is that-- is that crazy?

31:49.000 --> 31:51.250
It's just downstairs,
you know, casual.

31:52.333 --> 31:54.041
Oh, well...

31:55.166 --> 31:56.750
-I did have a plan.
-Oh.

31:57.666 --> 31:59.541
-Well, that's...
-But I could...

32:00.750 --> 32:02.166
I could just...

32:02.250 --> 32:04.625
-change it.
-Yeah? Okay.

32:04.708 --> 32:06.958
Great!
That-- I mean, that's terrific!

32:07.041 --> 32:09.458
I'll see you at seven o'clock.

32:09.541 --> 32:11.500
Okay. Oh!

32:11.583 --> 32:14.166
I'm Greg.
I should've started with that.

32:14.625 --> 32:15.875
(LAUGHS)

32:17.333 --> 32:19.083
I'm Tanya MacQuoid.

32:20.541 --> 32:21.708
Nice to meet you.

32:31.250 --> 32:32.958
(PHONE RINGS)

32:38.083 --> 32:39.333
This is the spa.

32:39.416 --> 32:41.208
TANYA:<i> Hey, it's me.</i>

32:41.291 --> 32:44.125
-Hey, Tanya.
-Uh, listen, um...

32:45.291 --> 32:48.708
Is it okay if we push off
our dinner till tomorrow?

32:48.791 --> 32:52.875
I-- I got asked out,
believe it or not.

32:52.958 --> 32:55.791
There's a deep-sea fisherman
staying next door.

32:55.875 --> 32:58.666
And he's with a group
from Black Lives Matter.

32:59.625 --> 33:00.958
Yeah?

33:01.041 --> 33:02.208
Sure, no problem.

33:02.291 --> 33:04.000
<i>I think a date</i>
<i>will be good for you.</i>

33:04.083 --> 33:05.291
Oh, yeah, well, I don't know.

33:05.375 --> 33:08.166
I'm not-- yeah, I'm not sure,
but yeah.

33:08.250 --> 33:11.666
I'm so sorry to put off
our dinner.

33:11.750 --> 33:12.916
BELINDA:<i> That's okay.</i>

33:13.000 --> 33:15.416
<i>You know, I got so excited</i>
<i>about our conversation,</i>

33:15.500 --> 33:17.750
<i>I decided to write up</i>
<i>a business proposal.</i>

33:17.833 --> 33:20.000
<i>I'm working on it now.</i>
<i>Have fun tonight.</i>

33:20.083 --> 33:22.375
TANYA: Oh. All right.
Well, hey. Thank you.

33:22.458 --> 33:23.916
-BELINDA:<i> Yeah. Yeah.</i>
-TANYA: All right.

33:24.000 --> 33:25.375
BELINDA:<i> Bye.</i>

33:25.458 --> 33:28.416
♪ (PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

33:44.250 --> 33:45.958
(SNIFFS)

33:46.041 --> 33:47.541
(PHONE RINGS)

33:49.208 --> 33:50.083
Hello?

33:50.166 --> 33:51.875
CHRISTIE:
<i>I have Mr. Patton on the line.</i>

33:51.958 --> 33:53.166
Oh, shit.

33:54.083 --> 33:55.250
Okay, yeah.

33:58.125 --> 33:59.541
-(LINE BEEPS)
-SHANE:<i> Hello.</i>

33:59.625 --> 34:01.625
Mr. Patton, are you enjoying
your mother?

34:01.708 --> 34:03.875
SHANE:<i> You said you were gonna</i>
<i>bring me that number</i>

34:04.000 --> 34:05.375
<i>of the general manager?</i>

34:06.250 --> 34:07.791
<i>You forgot to give it to me?</i>

34:07.875 --> 34:09.250
Yes, of course.
I'll get that to you.

34:09.333 --> 34:11.041
-Not a problem.
-SHANE:<i> Just bring it to dinner.</i>

34:11.125 --> 34:12.625
Bye-bye.

34:12.708 --> 34:14.916
Jesus Christ.
Fucking freak.

34:15.000 --> 34:16.333
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

34:16.791 --> 34:18.041
Just a minute!

34:19.625 --> 34:20.666
Yes?

34:23.083 --> 34:25.291
Oh, Dillon, come in.

34:25.375 --> 34:26.750
(DOOR CLOSES)

34:26.833 --> 34:28.958
I'm glad you're here.
I need to make a business card

34:29.041 --> 34:31.750
with the Lotus logo on it.
Are you any good with computers?

34:31.833 --> 34:34.500
Hey, listen,
the girls from the Tradewinds
are in the lobby.

34:34.583 --> 34:36.583
-What do they want?
-They wanna talk to you.

34:36.666 --> 34:39.000
Oh, fuck. All right.

34:39.083 --> 34:42.541
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

34:51.041 --> 34:52.541
ARMOND: Ladies.
How can I help you?

34:52.625 --> 34:54.166
There's stuff missing
from my bag.

34:54.250 --> 34:56.333
-What kind of stuff?
-Important stuff.

34:56.416 --> 34:58.041
Paula's medications.

34:58.125 --> 34:59.125
Oh, my.

35:00.750 --> 35:02.333
Well, if you'd like to make
an inventory

35:02.416 --> 35:04.500
of the medications
that you're missing,

35:04.583 --> 35:06.291
we can then do a proper search.

35:08.208 --> 35:10.583
Never mind.
There's too many to list.

35:12.125 --> 35:13.166
No?

